%Write a MATLAB program to generate a sinusoidal sequence x[n] = A * cos(omega_{2}*n + varphi) από plot the sequence using the 'stem' function. The input data the desired length L. 
%amplitude A_{n} the angular frequency and the phase o where 0 < omega_{2} < and 0 < varphi < 2pi with a sampling rate of 20 KHz.

clc; clear; close all;

% User inputs
L = input('Enter desired length L ( msec ): ');
A = input('Enter amplitude A: ');
w = input('Enter angular frequency w (rad/sample): ');
phi = input('Enter phase phi (0 < phi < 2*pi): ');

fs = 20 % Sampling Freq in Khz
n = 0:L-1;  
x = A * cos(w*n/fs + phi);

stem(n, x, 'filled');
xlabel('n');
ylabel('x[n]');
title('Sinusoidal Sequence');
grid on;
